  "number": 249,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/249",
  "title": "`debug.css` theme",
  "body": "Just a crazy idea I quickly hacked to help me debug BEM classes added. It adds an outline to every class starting with `ais-` and also display the name of the class when we hover it.\n\n![debugcss](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/10511570/5cc6a2e6-733a-11e5-9905-d2961f60f3a2.gif)\n\nHere is the current code:\n\n``` css\n[class^=ais-] {\n  outline: 1px solid red !important;\n  position:relative;\n}\n[class^=ais-]:hover:after {\n  position:absolute;\n  content:attr(class);\n  background: grey;\n  color: black;\n  padding:0.5rem;\n  font-size:1rem;\n  top:0;\n  white-space: nowrap;\n  z-index:10;\n  background:red;\n  left:0;\n  height:20px;\n}\n[class^=ais-] [class^=ais-] {\n  outline: 1px solid orange !important;\n  position:relative;\n}\n[class^=ais-] [class^=ais-]:hover:after {\n  z-index:100;\n  background: orange;\n  top:20px;\n}\n[class^=ais-] [class^=ais-] [class^=ais-] {\n  outline: 1px solid yellow !important;\n  position:relative;\n}\n[class^=ais-] [class^=ais-] [class^=ais-]:hover:after {\n  z-index:1000;\n  background: yellow;\n  top:40px;\n}\n```\n\nMaybe that is something we'd provide to theme creators, to help them see which class is used where.\n",
  "created_at": "2015-10-15T10:45:31Z",
